{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17493215","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17493215"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T07:00:54+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T07:00:54+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1257"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"1257","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/1257"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.11,0.13,0.18,0.13,0.45]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1257"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"44827"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"1257","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/1257"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1257"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"29714"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"10"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"78"},{"type":"tags","id":"188"},{"type":"tags","id":"688"},{"type":"tags","id":"1051"},{"type":"tags","id":"1091"},{"type":"tags","id":"1816"},{"type":"tags","id":"2777"},{"type":"tags","id":"3549"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"1670"},{"type":"contributions","id":"1743"},{"type":"contributions","id":"11474"},{"type":"contributions","id":"11574"},{"type":"contributions","id":"17070"},{"type":"contributions","id":"17992"},{"type":"contributions","id":"31028"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"44827","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/44827"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA35-year-old woman is admitted to a psychiatric hospital as an involuntary patient due to severe major depressive disorder with psychotic symptoms which has been worsening over the last three months. She has failed to show improvement on different antidepressants and antipsychotics. She has lost 5 kg weight in the last month alone and appears frail. Efforts to get her to eat and drink have failed since she believes that the voices in her head are telling her that she is letting a devil grow inside her and that she needs to kill it by not feeding it. She is currently 22 weeks pregnant with gestational hypertension and a current blood pressure of 150/100 mmHg. Her medical history includes the recent incidental finding cavernoma as well as hypothyroidism managed on levothyroxine. She is now refusing to take her oral medications.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn further review her eyes are sunken and she speaks with barely audible whispers. She reports she has been having morning headaches and feeling nauseated in the last two days. An assessment is made that she would benefit from treatment with electroconvulsive therapy (ECT), which has been approved by the Mental Health Tribunal, however, the patient keeps insisting that she does not want it.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following findings would constitute the strongest contraindication to ECT?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Her blood pressure","Her refusal of treatment","Pregnancy","Her hypothyroidism","The cavernoma"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EElectroconvulsive therapy (ECT) is an effective method to treat many psychiatric conditions including major depressive disorder, resistant schizophrenia, and bipolar disease. ECT is indicated in patients with a major depressive disorder with psychotic features that are refractory to treatment with antidepressants and antipsychotics, active suicidal tendencies, refusal to eat food, and when a rapid treatment of the underlying disorder is desired.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAccording to many studies, there are no absolute medical contraindications to ECT. However, there are several relative contraindications and medical evaluation is commonly performed to stabilise the patients before undergoing ECT. A few relative contraindications include: \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003Eraised intracranial pressure\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003Eintracranial lesions including infarction, hemorrhage, aneurysm, tumors\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003Esevere cardiovascular disease (e.g, recent myocardial infarction)\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003Ecochlear implant or cardiac pacemaker in situ\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003Ecardiac disease (decompensated heart failure, valvular disease, bradycardia, heart block)\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003Eepilepsy\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003Ethyrotoxicosis \u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAmong the answer choices provided in this item, the only relative contraindication to ECT is a space-occupying lesion (i.e., \u003Cstrong\u003Ecavernoma\u003C/strong\u003E) that is causing symptoms that could be associated with raised intracranial pressure\u003Cstrong\u003E \u003C/strong\u003Ei.e. headache, nausea as seen in this scenario. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHypothyroidism \u003C/strong\u003Eis not a relative contraindication, however, uncontrolled hyperthyroidism or thyrotoxicosis is considered a high risk situation. ECT can induce a thyroid storm in untreated hyperthyroidism and can induce a hypertensive crisis in pheochromocytoma.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EPatients with \u003Cstrong\u003Esevere hypertension\u003C/strong\u003E are recommended to undergo stabilisation of their blood pressure prior to ECT. However, hypertension in itself is not a contraindication to ECT.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERefusal to treatment\u003C/strong\u003E is not a contraindication to ECT. An authorised psychiatrist is able to apply to the Mental Health Tribunal for authority to perform a course of ECT on an adult patient if they do not have the capacity, or if the psychiatrist believes there is no less restrictive way for the patient to be treated, as seen within this scenario.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPregnancy\u003C/strong\u003E is not a contraindication for ECT. Pregnancy is an indication for ECT if the psychiatric condition poses an immediate risk to the mother and/or foetal life.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["ECT can be used in the emergency setting in patients with refractory major depressive disorder."],"references":["Electroconvulsive therapy and its different indications. Epilepsy and Psychiatry. 2008;10(1):105-117."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"29714"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1257"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"29714","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/29714"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-05-03T13:07:31+09:30","updatedAt":"2024-10-16T13:52:58+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1257"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"44827"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"10","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/10"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udfad","name":"Psychiatry","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:46+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"66","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/66"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Management","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"dat